 {"id":"remote_compilation_helper-i6x","title":"Task: Worker Telemetry Collection Agent (Network Metrics)","description":"## Overview
Implement network metrics collection for worker telemetry, reading from /proc/net/dev to track bandwidth utilization and network health for rsync transfers.

## Background and Justification
Network bandwidth affects RCH performance significantly:
- rsync file synchronization consumes upstream/downstream bandwidth
- Workers on slow networks increase total build time
- Network saturation can cause SSH timeouts and build failures

## Implementation Details

### Data Sources (Linux)
```rust
// Read from /proc/net/dev
// Format: Interface | bytes packets errs drop ... | bytes packets errs drop ...
//         eth0:  1234567890   12345    0    0 ...   987654321   9876    0    0 ...

pub struct NetDevStats {
    pub interface: String,
    pub rx_bytes: u64,
    pub rx_packets: u64,
    pub rx_errors: u64,
    pub rx_dropped: u64,
    pub tx_bytes: u64,
    pub tx_packets: u64,
    pub tx_errors: u64,
    pub tx_dropped: u64,
}

// Derived metrics from deltas
pub struct NetworkMetrics {
    pub rx_throughput_mbps: f64,      // (rx_bytes_delta * 8) / (elapsed_ms * 1000)
    pub tx_throughput_mbps: f64,      // (tx_bytes_delta * 8) / (elapsed_ms * 1000)
    pub rx_packets_per_sec: f64,
    pub tx_packets_per_sec: f64,
    pub error_rate: f64,              // (rx_errors + tx_errors) / total_packets
    pub drop_rate: f64,               // (rx_dropped + tx_dropped) / total_packets
}
```

### Interface Filtering
```rust
// Filter to physical interfaces, exclude:
// - lo (loopback)
// - docker*, veth* (container networking)
// - virbr* (libvirt bridges)

fn is_physical_interface(name: &str) -> bool {
    !name.starts_with("lo") &&
    !name.starts_with("docker") &&
    !name.starts_with("veth") &&
    !name.starts_with("virbr") &&
    !name.starts_with("br-")
}
```

### Connection Quality Metrics
```rust
// Optional: TCP connection stats from /proc/net/tcp
pub struct TcpStats {
    pub retransmit_rate: f64,  // Indicates network quality
    pub connection_count: u32,
}
```

